                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="99194" author="paf" created="Fri, 14 Nov 2014 18:11:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, Andreas - As you saw, I figured out the workaround right before you posted.  I appreciate the quick response.  I&apos;ll also review that patch...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="99189" author="adilger" created="Fri, 14 Nov 2014 17:11:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/12321&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/12321&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5707&quot; title=&quot;LFSCK 3: cannot load namespace LFSCK tracing file after downgrade from Lustre-2.7&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-5707&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-5707&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; should fix this bug. A separate patch to b2_5 will allow it to mount the filesystem even if there is a problem loading this file. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="99188" author="adilger" created="Fri, 14 Nov 2014 17:07:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Mount the MDT as type ldiskfs and delete the lfsck_namespace file. This is a bug in the current master code that is being fixed before release. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="99187" author="paf" created="Fri, 14 Nov 2014 17:07:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;lfsck_namespace file from the affected system.  Removing this file fixed the -ERANGE error.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="99186" author="paf" created="Fri, 14 Nov 2014 17:06:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It looks like the ERANGE is bubbling up out of xattr.c in ldiskfs, which I find worrying.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I was able to get the file system to start again by mounting the MDT as ldiskfs and removing the &apos;lfsck_namespace&apos;  file.  I&apos;ll attach that file here.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
